, and deeply held convictions to explore and define a coordinated vision for art, culture, and expression in American life.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aArt and societyzUnited States. 0aArt and statezUnited States. 0aArtsxEconomic aspectszUnited States. 0aArtsxPolitical aspectszUnited States. 0aCultural propertyzUnited States. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Popular Culture.2bisacsh  aamerican art.  aamerican artists.  aanalysis.  aarts education.  aclassical music.  acongress.  acopyright.  acreative.  acreativity.  acrisis.  acultural heritage.  acultural history.  acultural studies.  acultural.  aculture.  ademocracy.  afcc.  agovernment.  agreed.  aheritage.  amarketplace.  amemoir.  anational endowment for the arts.  anea grants.  anea.  aneglect.  apolicy.  apublic policy.  asocial history.  asocial studies.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052024112140uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093092640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520930926423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520930926/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY